title: High school roundup: SV shuts out Waverly to earn spot in sectional semis
text:
High school roundup: SV shuts out Waverly to earn spot in sectional semis 
By wbng sports October 20, 2015 Updated Oct 20, 2015 at 11:56 PM EDT 
Conklin, NY (WBNG Binghamton) Susquehanna Valley's three first half goals proved to be plenty as the Sabers shut out Waverly, 3-0, in the Section IV Class B girl's soccer quarterfinals on Tuesday. 
SV got goals from Torriana Graham, Lindsey Salisbury and Hannah Haskell on their way to the sectional semifinals. 
The Sabers will play the winner of Wednesday's game between Chenango Forks and Chenango Valley. 
Section IV girl's soccer playoff scores: Dryden 3 - Newark Valley 0Trumansburg 2 - Unatego 0
